This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category as it deals with interpretability in machine learning models, which is a key area of research in AI. The use of random walks over dynamic graphs also suggests a focus on graph-based machine learning, which is often studied in the cs.LG sub-category. The paper also deals with recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the cs.IR sub-category. The focus on user trust and privacy suggests a potential overlap with the cs.SI sub-category, which deals with social and information networks. Finally, the use of a crowdsourced user-study suggests a potential overlap with the cs.HC sub-category, which deals with human-computer interaction.
